<subSubSection id="C35AA3BC1E45FF7EF820FBE7197B25B0" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BFFF0371E45FF7EF820FBE716BE269A" blockId="2.[1977,2596,1116,1543]" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B9342C251E45FF7EF820FBE71769262C" bold="true" box="[2003,2158,1116,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF776FBE7177126F5" authority="Milne-Edwards, 1871" authorityName="Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1871" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Lagomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thibetanus">Lagomys thibetanus Milne-Edwards, 1871</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B28FA6A1E45FF7EF774FB3C16CD26F5" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3803698309" box="[2183,2506,1159,1188]" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">“Moupin [= Baoxing],”</materialsCitation>
Baoxing County, Ya’an, Sichuan, China.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFFF0371E45FF7EF821FB61152627E9" blockId="2.[1977,2596,1116,1543]" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">
According to mtDNA, 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF6C8FB6116E326A2" baseAuthorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[2363,2532,1242,1267]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thibetana">O. thibetana</taxonomicName>
belongs to subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF72AFB421656274B" authorityName="Link" authorityYear="1795" box="[2265,2385,1273,1306]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ochotona</taxonomicName>
. Together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF825FA9217552713" authorityName="Lyon" authorityYear="1907" box="[2006,2130,1321,1346]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cansus">O. cansus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF769FA92160B2713" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1911" box="[2202,2316,1321,1346]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="syrinx">O. syrinx</taxonomicName>
, it forms a morphologically homogeneous group, difficult to identify. Up to the late 20™ century, all | three species were united as 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF68FFA2C151B27E9" baseAuthorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[2428,2588,1431,1464]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thibetana">O. thibetana</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFFF0371E45FF7EF827FA79197B25B0" blockId="2.[1977,2596,1116,1543]" lastBlockId="2.[1391,2600,1550,3277]" pageId="2" pageNumber="30">
Existence of wide sympatry zones and cranial differences between 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF6B1FA5D16E52456" baseAuthorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[2370,2530,1510,1543]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thibetana">O. thibetana</taxonomicName>
and those two species led to separation ofall three taxa. Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF6BBF9B516E4247E" baseAuthorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[2376,2531,1550,1583]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thibetana">O. thibetana</taxonomicName>
represents a compact, clearly separated taxon; studies of mtDNA show deep divergence between local populations. Singular mtDNA sequences do not form a monophyletic clade. Taxon morosa is usually aggregated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF7EBF93F179F24F4" authorityName="Lyon" authorityYear="1907" box="[2072,2200,1668,1701]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cansus">O. cansus</taxonomicName>
, and it morphologically resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EFA18F914198F249D" baseAuthorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[1515,1672,1711,1740]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thibetana">O. thibetana</taxonomicName>
; however,it is closer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF82AF9141753249D" authorityName="Lyon" authorityYear="1907" box="[2009,2132,1711,1740]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cansus">O. cansus</taxonomicName>
based on the analysis of singular mtDNA sequences. According to morphological study, it includes nanggenica, sikimaria, and zappey:. Usually, sacraria is listed as subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF7B4F94117E5254A" baseAuthorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[2119,2274,1786,1819]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thibetana">O. thibetana</taxonomicName>
, but the type specimen of sacraria belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF96DF89918172512" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1911" box="[1694,1808,1826,1859]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="syrinx">O. syrinx</taxonomicName>
. Study of singular mtDNA sequences suggests a separate taxonomic position of sikimaria. Provisional subspecies are recognized here, but they need further revision. 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF943F8CB18A225C0" baseAuthorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[1712,1957,1904,1937]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thibetana">Ochotona thibetana</taxonomicName>
is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF751F8CB161325C0" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1911" box="[2210,2324,1904,1937]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="syrinx">O. syrinx</taxonomicName>
in peripheral parts of Hengduan Mountains in Sichuan and widely with 
<taxonomicName id="4C408BB41E45FF7EF7ACF82317DC25E8" authorityName="Lyon" authorityYear="1907" box="[2143,2267,1944,1977]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cansus">O. cansus</taxonomicName>
in Sichuan. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
